New version of the WebGlossary.
The plan is to implement the WebGlossary without relational database, using MongoDB.

1. Configuring and starting MongoDB
===================================
Grails script doesn't start or stop them mongodb database server, you should be perform this manually.
If you're not familiar with MongoDB (like me) some help to configure and start mongodb to the application:

1.1 Download MongoDB
--------------------
Visit to http://www.mongodb.org/downloads

1.2 Start the database server
-----------------------------
Visit to http://www.mongodb.org/display/DOCS/Quickstart

1.3 Creating Witty development database
---------------------------------
Run the following command in the WittyProject/mongodb directory:
    mongo localhost:27017/witty-dev --quiet create-mongodb.js